    "content" : "Brian\n<br>\n<br>You're not going to like this but an intermittent problem like that is going to be a pain in the arse to find, guess it could be something simple like a loose coil connection, would suggest checking all the spade connectors on the leads as if it is cutting out it has to be something common to all cylinders and not just say one HT lead.\n<br>\n<br>Guess it could be the fuel solenoid if you have a single carb or again maybe the electrical spade connector or wire that feeds it.\n<br>\n<br>A starter for 10 for you.\n<br>\n<br>Richard",
